metadata.title: Ryan Navion
aws::graph::propositions: # Ryan Navion Aircraft Variants
North American NA-143 is a variant of the Ryan Navion.
North American NA-143 consisted of two prototypes.
North American NA-145 Navion is a variant of the Ryan Navion.
North American NA-145 Navion was built by North American.
North American NA-145 Navion had 1,027 aircraft built.
North American NA-154 Navion is a variant of the Ryan Navion.
North American NA-154 Navion is a military version for the United States Army.
North American NA-154 Navion was designated as the L-17A by the United States Army.
North American NA-154 Navion had 83 aircraft built.
Ryan Navion is an aircraft built by Ryan.
Ryan Navion had 600 aircraft built.
Ryan Navion A is an improved variant of the Ryan Navion.
Ryan Navion A has a 205 horsepower Continental E-185-9 engine.
Ryan Navion A had 602 aircraft built.
Ryan Navion B is a modified variant of the Ryan Navion.
Ryan Navion B has a 260 horsepower Lycoming GO-435-C2 engine.
Ryan Navion B is also known as the Super Navion 260.
Ryan Navion B had 222 aircraft built.
Tusco Navion D is a conversion of the Ryan Navion.
Tusco Navion D was converted by Tulsa Manufacturing Company.
Tusco Navion D has a 240 horsepower Continental IO-470-P engine.
Tusco Navion D has tip tanks.
Tusco Navion E is a conversion of the Ryan Navion.
Tusco Navion E was converted by Tulsa Manufacturing Company.
Tusco Navion E has a 250 horsepower Continental IO-470-C engine.
Tusco Navion E has tip tanks.
Tusco Navion F is a conversion of the Ryan Navion.
Tusco Navion F was converted by Tulsa Manufacturing Company.
Tusco Navion F has a 260 horsepower Continental IO-470-H engine.
Tusco Navion F has tip tanks.

text:
## Variants

North American NA-143
Two prototypes.
North American NA-145 Navion
North-American-built production aircraft, 1,027 built.
North American NA-154 Navion
Military version for the United States Army as the L-17A, 83 built.
Ryan Navion
Ryan-built production aircraft, 600 built.

Ryan Navion A
Improved Navion with a 205hp Continental E-185-9 engine, 602 built.
Ryan Navion B
Modified for the higher powered 260hp Lycoming GO-435-C2 engine, also known as the Super Navion 260, 222 built.
Tusco Navion D

Conversion by Tulsa Manufacturing Company with a 240hp Continental IO-470-P engine and tip tanks.
Tusco Navion E
Conversion Tulsa Manufacturing Company with a 250hp Continental IO-470-C engine and tip tanks.
Tusco Navion F
Conversion Tulsa Manufacturing Company with a 260hp Continental IO-470-H engine and tip tanks.
